Microservices:
    1.Microservices a variant of service-based-architecture(SOA),arranges an application as a collection of loosely coupled isolated services.
    2.Microservices is a unique method of software development that focuses on developing isolated individual services combines as a single application.
    3.Microservices help to build an application as combination of multiple small services,each running in its own environment and are independently deployable.
    4.These services can be written in different programming languages and also have its own storage and databases.
    5.Changes done to one service will not have any downtime on other services,which also enables developers to release there changes without any dependency on other services.
Microservices Advantages:
    1.It gives developers freedom to develop and deploy services independently
    2.These independent services can be developed using different programming languages.
    3.When new changes are required,it only needs to be done to specific services only instead of bring down whole application.
    4.It provides better fault tolerance,where one service going on does not have much impact on whole application.
Microservices Disadvantages:
    1.Due to multiple services,it becomes sometimes complicated to perform end to end testing.
    2.Developers need to put additional efforts to establish connectivity between multiple services.
    3.With multiple services utilization of resources would also increase.
    4.Debugging errors for services can be harder since each service has its own service logs.
