What is Blue-Green Deployment?
    Deploy new version in parallel(Green) keep old version(Blue).Switch traffic once stable.Ensures zero downtime.
    Definition

        Blue-Green Deployment is a software deployment strategy where you maintain two identical environments:

        🔵 Blue → Current live (production) version
        🟢 Green → New version (updated app)

👉 Instead of updating the live system directly, you deploy the new version separately and then switch traffic.

    🧠 Simple idea:

        Don’t update the running system — prepare a new one and switch when ready

    🔄 How it works (Step-by-step)

        Users are using Blue (current version)
        You deploy new version to Green
        Test Green thoroughly
        Switch traffic from Blue → Green
        Green becomes live 🎉
    🌍 Real-world analogy
            🎭 Two stages in a theater
                    Stage 1 (Blue) → current performance
                    Stage 2 (Green) → next show being prepared

            👉 Once ready:
                    Lights switch to Stage 2
                    Audience sees new show instantly

            🧾 Example Scenario
                🛒 E-commerce website
                    Without Blue-Green:
                        Update happens live
                        Users may see:
                            errors ❌
                            downtime ❌

            With Blue-Green:
                    Blue → running current website
                    Green → deploy new version (new UI, features)

            👉 After testing:

                Switch traffic to Green
                Users see new version instantly
            ⚡ Key Benefit: Zero Downtime

            👉 Users don’t experience:
                    crashes
                    maintenance screens
            🔁 Rollback (Very Important)

                If something goes wrong:

                    👉 Switch back to Blue instantly

            🌍 Real-world analogy:

                    Like switching TV channels:

                        Channel A (Blue) → current
                        Channel B (Green) → new

                    👉 If problem → switch back immediately

                    💻 Conceptual Python Example (Traffic Switch)

                    def blue_environment():
                        return "Old Version Running"

                    def green_environment():
                        return "New Version Running"

                    # Switch control
                    current_env = blue_environment

                    print(current_env())   # Old version

                    # Deploy new version and switch
                    current_env = green_environment

                    print(current_env())   # New version
            🎯 Benefits
                    ✅ Zero downtime
                    🔄 Easy rollback
                    🧪 Safe testing in production-like environment
                    🚀 Smooth releases
            ⚠️ Challenges:

                    ❌ Requires double infrastructure
                    ❌ Cost can be higher
                    ❌ Data synchronization needed

            🧠 When to use it?
                    High-traffic apps
                    Critical systems (banking, e-commerce)
                    When downtime is unacceptable

